{"type":"compaction","id":"84ddccd8","parentId":"0d915edb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:02:35.436Z","summary":"## Goal\nConfigure the assistant/system so every reply and progress update follows the user’s required Thai format, enforced by real config/source changes rather than relying only on AI memory. Also make Hermes behave like this assistant “ทุกอย่าง” including form, mode analysis, tool/MCP gate, footer/session display, token-saving/session behavior, and automatic temporary monitoring jobs for long-running/waiting SocratiCode tasks that notify completion and delete themselves/no junk files. Now additionally add RTK support into Hermes (Hermes‑native, not referencing the assistant/OpenClaw workspace).\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User wants replies in exact header format: `🧑🏼‍💻[GPT 5.5] [คำถามทั่วไป] 🧑🏼‍💻`\n- Footer now includes short session form: `Session: (8%)` after RTK.\n- `Tokens:` must reflect real overall API/model context usage including hidden/system/tool/history context, not only user-typed text.\n- `Cache:` means cache hit percentage for reused context; not the same as Session.\n- `Session:` means current context/session usage percentage.\n- Do not change the user’s form.\n- Every progress/status message must also follow the required form.\n- Before any tool / MCP / command in every message: must first analyze mode and list tools/MCP/commands to be used.\n- For “หมวดทำงาน”, assistant must first state category, tools/NCT/MCP to use, and what will be changed before executing.\n- Hermes-related work requires explicit permission first; user previously granted “อนุญาต”.\n- Must use SocratiCode before code/config work when applicable.\n- Prefer low-token workflow: search/excerpt/truncate over full logs/files.\n- User wants rolling 2-session retention: keep latest session + previous session as backup; when a new session is created, delete only the oldest so 2 remain.\n- For Hermes work, user explicitly requires writing/implementing inside Hermes, not referencing/depending on files in the assistant/OpenClaw workspace.\n- When SocratiCode or similar background work is waiting/running, create an automatic temporary cron/job/monitor so user knows when it will finish or that it finished, then auto-delete the job/files after completion.\n- RTK addition to Hermes must be Hermes-native (no dependency on workspace files).\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Added persistent progress-notification rule to `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md`\n- [x] Added same rule to `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md` (now includes auto monitor job rule)\n- [x] Confirmed inserted rules with `grep`\n- [x] Inspected Hermes/OpenClaw config and gateway code via SocratiCode/search\n- [x] Found `display.runtime_footer.enabled: false` in `/home/apinan/.hermes/config.yaml`\n- [x] Found `gateway/runtime_footer.py` only supports footer, not full required envelope\n- [x] Added backup files with suffix `.bak-response-envelope-20260510-191127`\n- [x] Added `enforce_response_envelope()` to `/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/runtime_footer.py`\n- [x] Patched `/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py` to call `enforce_response_envelope()` before final send\n- [x] Enabled config block `display.response_envelope.enabled: true` in `/home/apinan/.hermes/config.yaml`\n- [x] Ran `py_compile` checks successfully\n- [x] Tested envelope wrapping and fixed emoji ZWJ issue from `🧑🏼💻` to `🧑🏼‍💻`\n- [x] Patched `runtime_footer.py` so valid headers must start like `🧑🏼‍💻[MODEL] [CATEGORY] 🧑🏼‍💻`\n- [x] Updated generated header format to `🧑🏼‍💻[GPT 5.5] [สรุป] 🧑🏼‍💻`\n- [x] Added footer/session preference in behavior: `Session: (8%)`\n- [x] Explained `Cache` vs `Session` to user.\n- [x] Saved rolling 2-session retention preference in `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md`\n- [x] User pointed out assistant used tools before analyzing command; assistant acknowledged error.\n- [x] Added strict Tool/MCP Gate to `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md`\n- [x] Added strict Tool/MCP Gate to `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md`\n- [x] SocratiCode indexed `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace`\n- [x] SocratiCode impact check showed `AGENTS.md` and `MEMORY.md` blast radius 0.\n- [x] SocratiCode index updated after editing `AGENTS.md` and `MEMORY.md`\n- [x] Gateway appears recovered/running after earlier restart/draining; later `session_status` showed gateway uptime increasing.\n- [x] Added Hermes-native override rules to `/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md`\n- [x] Created `/home/apinan/.hermes/AGENTS.md` as Hermes-native project context/backup rules\n- [x] Confirmed `/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md` and `/home/apinan/.hermes/AGENTS.md` contain the override rules (including auto‑monitor‑job rule).\n- [x] Added permanent auto‑monitor‑job rule to four files: `/mnt/c/…/AGENTS.md`, `/mnt/c/…/MEMORY.md`, `/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md`, `/home/apinan/.hermes/AGENTS.md`\n- [x] Tested the temporary monitor mechanism: created cron job `watch-hermes-socraticode-index-self-cleanup` (ID `8535c5ca-15ff-416e-9192-8410aa55699e`) to watch `/home/apinan/.hermes` SocratiCode indexing → indexing finished → cron auto‑removed via `cron remove` → confirmed `jobs: 0` with no junk.\n- [x] Verified Hermes SocratiCode indexing completed (`status green`, `chunks 71023`, `file watcher active`).\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Add RTK into Hermes (Hermes‑native, not referencing workspace). Permission granted (`ได้`). Plan: read hermes‑permission skill → SocratiCode inspect Hermes config/gateway → edit → py_compile/grep check.\n\n### Blocked\n- No blockers currently.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use system-side enforcement**: User explicitly rejected relying only on AI self-discipline; patch must be in source/config.\n- **Do not use `post_llm_call` for mutation**: Hermes docs say `post_llm_call` return values are ignored.\n- **Patch send path instead**: `gateway/run.py` is the final response path where footer/envelope can be enforced.\n- **Preserve reply tags**: `enforce_response_envelope()` preserves `[[reply_to...]]` tags before wrapping.\n- **Exact format correction required**: Header must be bracketed exactly like `🧑🏼‍💻[GPT 5.5] [คำถามทั่วไป] 🧑🏼‍💻`.\n- **Tool/MCP Gate required**: Every message must first classify mode and disclose intended tools/MCP/commands before using them.\n- **Hermes must be standalone**: User does not want Hermes to read/use assistant/OpenClaw workspace rule files because names like OpenClaw would confuse him.\n- **Session retention preference**: Keep rolling 2 sessions: latest + previous backup; delete oldest only when a new one exists.\n- **Temporary monitor jobs**: For long-running SocratiCode/background waits, create a temporary cron/job/monitor, notify when done, then delete the job/files automatically to avoid junk. Tested successfully.\n- **RTK addition plan**: Implement RTK in Hermes-native files only (`/home/apinan/.hermes`), using SocratiCode first, then editing, no reference to workspace.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Start RTK implementation: read `hermes-permission` skill (already done), then SocratiCode inspect Hermes config/gateway (likely `/home/apinan/.hermes/config.yaml` and relevant gateway files) to determine where RTK can be enabled.\n2. After inspection, edit the minimal necessary Hermes files to enable RTK, compile-check, and confirm behavior.\n3. Keep the strict Tool/MCP Gate and envelope form in all progress messages.\n4. Avoid touching workspace files for this Hermes‑side change.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Temporary cron `8535c5ca-15ff-416e-9192-8410aa55699e` removed after indexing finished; no residual jobs.\n- Hermes SocratiCode index complete (`green, 71023 chunks`).\n- Latest user request: “ใส่rtk ลงไปใน hermesด้วยนะ” – add RTK to Hermes itself.\n- Assistant already obtained explicit permission and will proceed in Hermes‑native manner without relying on the assistant workspace.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user requested modification of the Hermes system configuration to integrate RTK (Rust Token Killer) for permanent token savings on terminal commands.\n\n## Early Progress\n- **Workflow followed**: SocratiCode → impact assessment → read/edit → verification\n- **Files analyzed**: AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, config.yaml (all in `/home/apinan/.hermes/`)\n- **Key findings before edits**:\n  - Hermes had token-saving policies but no explicit RTK command rules\n  - `rtk_label` was set to `system-enforced` in config.yaml (line 339)\n  - No existing RTK skill in Hermes's skills directory\n  - Impact analysis showed AGENTS.md and SOUL.md had 0 dependents\n\n- **Edits made**:\n  1. **AGENTS.md & SOUL.md**: Inserted `## RTK Command Policy — required` block after the existing token-saving needle, mandating `rtk` prefix for terminal commands (git, build, test, lint, docker, etc.) with fallback to raw + filtering\n  2. **config.yaml**: Changed `rtk_label: system-enforced` → `rtk_label: enabled`\n  3. **Created new skill**: `/home/apinan/.hermes/skills/devops/rtk-integration/SKILL.md` with quick reference and fallback rules\n\n- **Verification performed**:\n  - YAML config parsed successfully (valid)\n  - RTK version confirmed: 0.39.0\n  - RTK gain stats checked: 6.0% savings across 34,395 commands\n  - Grep confirmed all 4 files contain the expected changes\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe suffix shows the final verification step: checking SocratiCode index status for Hermes and listing existing cron jobs. The codebase graph is still building (13/13 chunks embedded, 100%, building code graph phase). No cron jobs currently exist. The assistant intends to create a self-cleaning cron job to monitor index completion and notify the user when done, per Hermes behavior rules.\n\n<read-files>\n/home/apinan/.hermes/MEMORY.md\n/home/apinan/.hermes/USER.md\n/home/apinan/.hermes/config.yaml\n/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py\n/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/runtime_footer.py\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n~/.openclaw/skills/rtk-integration/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/apinan/.hermes/AGENTS.md\n/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"0234cf5a","tokensBefore":46214,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/apinan/.hermes/MEMORY.md","/home/apinan/.hermes/USER.md","/home/apinan/.hermes/config.yaml","/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py","/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/runtime_footer.py","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md","~/.openclaw/skills/rtk-integration/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/apinan/.hermes/AGENTS.md","/home/apinan/.hermes/SOUL.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md"]},"fromHook":false}
