{"type":"message","id":"b29d0998","parentId":"88d8a740","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:06:09.748Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check the OpenClaw config for model routing setup. The `openclaw.json` seems to list available models but I need to see the actual config structure with defaults. Let me look at the full config.\n\nAlso I notice the current model is `ollama-pay/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud` which is a fallback, not GPT 5.5. The session status earlier showed `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` but now it's on deepseek. This means GPT 5.5 may have been the original primary model, and when it ran out of credits/usage, it fell back to deepseek.\n\nWait, looking at MEMORY.md: \"Primary model: minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\". But the session previously ran on `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` and now is on `ollama-pay/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud`.\n\nThe user said GPT 5.5 is \"หมดไปแล้ว\" - exhausted. So the question is why did it run out so fast?\n\nLet me look at how models are routed. The config shows many models available. Let me check if there's a specific model assignment for this session.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the session_status earlier in the summary:\n- It showed `Model: openai-codex/gpt-5.5`\n- Usage: 5h 0% left\n\nSo GPT 5.5 has an hourly limit of ~5 hours or some credit system and it's been exhausted.\n\nNow the session is on deepseek-v4-pro:cloud (fallback).\n\nThe real question from the user: WHY did GPT 5.5 run out so fast?\n\nKey factors I should analyze:\n1. The session has 5 compactions - meaning the context was very large multiple times\n2. Each compaction means the context window filled up → large amounts of tokens used\n3. The user already trimmed AGENTS/SOUL/IDENTITY/USER/TOOLS/MEMORY files which saved ~58.7% of context\n4. But the system still used up GPT 5.5 fast\n\nLet me look at what's actually consuming tokens. The key culprits could be:\n- The compacted summary itself is very large (the entire conversation history compressed into a summary)\n- Tool outputs and context files still add up\n- The session has been running for a long time with many tool calls\n- Each turn includes the full compacted summary + project context files\n\nLet me check the config more carefully to understand the model routing.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_63lzpkam","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\n# Show agents.defaults section\ndefaults = d.get('agents',{}).get('defaults',{})\nprint('=== agents.defaults ===')\nfor k,v in defaults.items():\n    if k != 'models':\n        print(f'{k}: {json.dumps(v, indent=2)[:300]}')\nprint()\nprint('=== model routing ===')\nprint('defaultModel:', defaults.get('model'))\nprint('imageGenModel:', defaults.get('imageGenerationModel',{}).get('primary'))\nprint('models count:', len(defaults.get('models',{})))\n# Check if thinking is configured\nprint('thinking:', d.get('agents',{}).get('defaults',{}).get('thinking'))\nprint()\n# Check session-level overrides\nprint('=== session overrides ===')\nfor k,v in d.items():\n    if 'session' in str(k).lower():\n        print(f'{k}: {str(v)[:200]}')\n\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ktm1v7lp","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprov = d.get('providers',{})\nprint('=== providers ===')\nfor pname,pconf in prov.items():\n    print(f'{pname}:', json.dumps({k:v for k,v in pconf.items() if k not in ('models',)}, indent=2)[:200])\n\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778418344233,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778418353689"}}
