{"type":"message","id":"3abd4eca","parentId":"0edaf108","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:06:50.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture. Let me analyze:\n\n1. **Primary model**: `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` - this should be the first used model\n2. **Fallbacks**: `deepseek-v4-pro:cloud` → `gemini-3-flash-preview:cloud` → `qwen3.5:397b-cloud`\n3. **GPT 5.5 is NOT in the default fallback chain** - it's a separate model\n4. **Compaction settings**: keep 1000 recent tokens, reserve 3000 tokens, truncate after compaction\n5. **Context pruning**: cache-ttl mode with 1min TTL, keep last 2 assistants, trim ratios set\n\nNow, the current session shows model `ollama-pay/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud` - this is the first fallback. This means:\n- MiniMax-M2.7 failed or was exhausted first\n- Then deepseek-v4-pro is now active\n\nBUT the user is asking about GPT 5.5 being \"หมด\" (exhausted). GPT 5.5 is `openai-codex/gpt-5.5`. This isn't in the fallback chain. So how was GPT 5.5 being used?\n\nLooking at the session_status from earlier in the summary:\n- It showed `Model: openai-codex/gpt-5.5`\n- Usage: 5h 0% left\n\nSo at some point, the session was using GPT 5.5 as the main model. The current session now shows deepseek-v4-pro. So what happened between then and now?\n\nPossibilities:\n1. The user or assistant manually switched to GPT 5.5 using `/model` or `session_status` with model override\n2. GPT 5.5 was set as a session-level model override\n3. The compact summary mentions the user wanted the header to say `[GPT 5.5]` - this was just a display preference, not necessarily wanting to USE GPT 5.5\n\nWait, looking at the summary more carefully:\n- \"Current model display: openai-codex/gpt-5.5 → GPT 5.5\"\n- This was in MEMORY.md as a display mapping, not a model activation\n\nBut then the runtime also listed GPT 5.5 as the active model. So someone/something switched the session to GPT 5.5.\n\nThe key question: WHY is the user burning through expensive models so fast?\n\nBased on the config:\n1. The compaction keeps only 1000 recent tokens + reserves 3000 for reply - this is very tight\n2. But 5 compactions have happened already, meaning the context filled up many times\n3. Each time context fills, it means LOTS of tokens were consumed\n\nThe root cause likely includes:\n1. **Project context files** - AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md are all injected every turn (though trimmed now)\n2. **The compacted summary itself** - the summary in this turn is VERY long and full of details\n3. **Tool outputs** - even with pruning, tool outputs consume tokens\n4. **5 compactions** = 5 times the context window filled up → massive token usage\n5. **Thinking mode** is set to `medium` - this adds hidden thinking tokens\n\nLet me calculate roughly:\n- The compacted summary in this conversation was about 8-10k tokens\n- Project context files add several thousand more\n- 5 compactions × ~200k tokens each = roughly 1M tokens potentially used\n- Plus all the tool outputs\n\nThe user needs to understand:\n1. Why GPT 5.5 ran out (if it was being used)\n2. How to prevent this in the future\n\nLet me also check if there's a session-level model override that set GPT 5.5.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the current session shows `ollama-pay/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud` as the model. This is the first fallback. The primary `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` must have failed/exhausted. \n\nThe user is complaining about GPT 5.5 being exhausted. Looking at the earlier session status in the summary: \"Model: openai-codex/gpt-5.5\". So the session was running on GPT 5.5 before. Now it's on deepseek. This means GPT 5.5 was exhausted and it fell through... but wait, GPT 5.5 isn't in the fallback chain. \n\nLet me think about this differently. The session might have been explicitly set to GPT 5.5 via `/model` or session_status model override. Then GPT 5.5 ran out of credits. Then the session fell back... but the fallback chain doesn't include GPT 5.5, so maybe it fell to the configured fallbacks (deepseek etc).\n\nOr maybe it's a different scenario - the user is talking about a SEPARATE usage of GPT 5.5 (like in ChatGPT directly, or in another session), not this OpenClaw session.\n\nActually, the user said \"GPT 5.5 ถึงยังหมดไปตอนนี้คือมันหมดไปแล้ว\" - GPT 5.5 is already exhausted NOW. And \"ทำไม...ถึงยังหมดไปอีกแล้ว\" - why did it run out AGAIN.\n\nI think the core question is: the user is trying to save tokens, made various optimizations, but the models are still running out fast. The user wants to understand WHY and WHERE they went wrong.\n\nLet me provide a clear analysis of what's consuming tokens based on what I can see:\n\n1. **This session has been running for ~47 minutes** (gateway uptime 46m 48s) \n2. **5 compactions** in that time = context filled up 5 times\n3. **The compacted summary** is huge (~8-10k tokens) and gets included every turn\n4. **Project context files** add up\n5. **Thinking mode (medium)** uses hidden tokens\n6. **Tool outputs** from SocratiCode, config reads, etc. add up\n7. **Model routing** - when primary fails, fallbacks are used, and each one has its own cost\n\nThe user needs practical advice. Let me look at the actual token flow to give concrete numbers.\n\nActually, let me just give a clear, concise analysis. The user is frustrated, so I should be direct and helpful.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ijqzz6nh","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\n# Check current session config\nsessions = d.get('sessions',{})\nfor k,v in sessions.items():\n    if 'main' in str(k):\n        print(f'{k}: {json.dumps(v, indent=2)[:500]}')\nprint('---')\n# Check any model overrides\nagents = d.get('agents',{})\nfor agent_id, agent_conf in agents.items():\n    if agent_id == 'defaults': continue\n    model = agent_conf.get('model')\n    if model:\n        print(f'Agent {agent_id} model: {model}')\n\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778418369816,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778418381889"}}
