{"type":"message","id":"ae12acbc","parentId":"3e75a54d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:13:31.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"แก้ได้ไหม\" - can you fix it? The thinking is still showing \"medium\" even though I changed thinkingDefault to \"off\" and restarted. But the restart seems to not have fully taken effect - the uptime only went from 52m to 53m (about 1 minute passed), which could be either a fresh restart or just a timing thing.\n\nBut the Think is still \"medium\" - so the config change might not have taken effect. Let me check if the config was actually saved correctly and if a proper restart is needed.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the gateway restart command was aborted by SIGTERM. This suggests the process was terminated but maybe not cleanly restarted. The uptime went from 52m to 53m, so it has only been running for about 1 minute. So the restart DID happen.\n\nBut thinking is still \"medium\". This could mean:\n1. The config change didn't persist properly\n2. The thinking setting is cached and needs another restart\n3. The session-level override is separate from the default\n\nActually wait - thinking is a SESSION-level setting, not just a config default. When the gateway restarts, the SESSION still has its own thinking setting which might have been \"medium\" at session start. The thinkingDefault in config only applies to NEW sessions, not existing ones.\n\nSo the issue is: I changed the default for future sessions, but the CURRENT session still has \"medium\" thinking.\n\nTo fix this for the current session, I need to either:\n1. Start a new session (which would use the new default of \"off\")\n2. Find a way to change the session-level thinking setting\n\nLet me try to find if there's a way to change thinking for the current session. Maybe I can use the /thinking command if I send it as a message...\n\nActually, from OpenClaw docs, `/thinking` is a slash command that can be used to toggle thinking. Let me try sending this as a message into the session.\n \nThe thinking parameter for agentTurn in the cron/job system shows \"off\" as a valid option, and the session_status schema has a model parameter but not thinking. However, the thinking setting is fundamentally tied to the session runtime itself, not something I can override through agentTurn. The current thinking value is stored in the session state, so unless OpenClaw provides a way to modify it mid-session, I'd likely need to start fresh to apply the \"off\" default.","thinkingSignature":"103e321e87c4399df82c1155da24dc8e86c0cb812eb1693ee0736b87817545ca"},{"type":"text","text":"\nRestart ไม่ถึง 1 นาที (uptime 53m) แต่ Think ยัง medium — เพราะ `thinkingDefault` ใน config ใช้กับ session ใหม่เท่านั้น session ปัจจุบันยังคงค่าเดิม\n\nต้องเริ่ม session ใหม่ถึงจะได้ thinking=off\n\n🧑🏼‍💻[GPT 5.5] [ทำงาน] 🧑🏼‍💻\nตอนนี้ครับเจ้านาย → session ปัจจุบันยัง medium อยู่ แก้ได้ 2 ทาง:\n\n**ทาง 1:** สั่ง `/thinking off` เองใน Telegram แล้วผมจะตอบรับ\n\n**ทาง 2:** ผมสร้าง session ใหม่ให้เจ้านาย (session ใหม่จะใช้ thinkingDefault=off อัตโนมัติ)\n\nสั่งเลยครับว่าจะทางไหน\n[Tokens: น้อย | Cache: 98% | RTK: - | Session: 23%] 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":203,"output":875,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":37745,"totalTokens":38823,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778418788868,"responseId":"064fb76677389550c0edcfedb0f90c41"}}
